20000522123800000_1	BLACK BOXES FOR CARS RAISE PRIVACY CONCERNS.	black box car rais privaci concern
20000522123800000_2	Black boxes for cars a technology borrowed from the airline industry now are poised to help auto accident investigators pin the blame on drivers responsible for causing crashes.	black box car technolog borrow airlin industri pois help auto accid investig pin blame driver respons caus crash
20000522123800000_3	Since 1990 many General Motors and Ford cars and trucks have been equipped with a device similar to an airliner s black box or flight data recorder which automatically records the vehicle s speed throttle setting braking effort and engine rpm for each of the five seconds leading to an air bag deployment.	sinc mani gener motor ford car truck equip devic similar airlin black box flight data record automat record vehicl speed throttl set brake effort engin rpm five second lead air bag deploy
20000522123800000_4	Until now however it was difficult to extract that information from the car s air bag control module.	howev wa difficult extract inform car air bag control modul
20000522123800000_5	But a California company in March began selling a device that connects a car s onboard computer to a laptop computer to quickly extract such key information from a crashed vehicle.	california compani march began sell devic connect car onboard comput laptop comput quickli extract key inform crash vehicl
20000522123800000_6	The 2 500 device called a Crash Data Retrieval System is being marketed to police departments insurance companies and auto rental agencies to help them reconstruct crashes to determine fault.	devic call crash data retriev system market polic depart insur compani auto rental agenc help reconstruct crash determin fault
20000522123800000_7	The system lets investigators collect objective accurate data on crashes to enhance reconstruction (of accidents) said Jim Zaleski president of Santa Barbara based Vetronix Corp.	system let investig collect object accur data crash enhanc reconstruct accid said jim zaleski presid santa barbara base vetronix corp
20000522123800000_8	This opens the door to a new generation of understanding and modeling automobile accidents he said.	thi open door new gener understand model automobil accid said
20000522123800000_9	Some of the vehicles that have the capability to provide such data also can tell investigators whether the car s occupants were wearing seatbelts and whether the passenger side air bag had been deactivated.	vehicl capabl provid data also tell investig whether car occup wear seat belt whether passeng side air bag deactiv
20000522123800000_10	Most of the data that the system gives to crash investigators isn t new such information has been used for decades to reconstruct accidents said Phil Haseltine president of the Automotive Coalition for Traffic Safety an auto industry funded group.	data system give crash investig new inform ha use decad reconstruct accid said phil haseltin presid automot coalit traffic safeti auto industri fund group
20000522123800000_11	But investigators had to gather the information using other sources such as tire skid marks in the past.	investig gather inform use sourc tire skid mark past
20000522123800000_12	This technology isn t measuring anything new but it is measuring it more accurately than in the past he said.	thi technolog measur anyth new measur accur past said
20000522123800000_13	On the engineering side it will help the design engineer find out whether safety systems work as well in real crashes as they do in laboratory crash tests.	engin side help design engin find whether safeti system work well real crash laboratori crash test
